1.title: Leak 1.0: The House, His Aunt, Her Caregiver, the Abuse, the Gun, the Arrest
1.plot: Leak 1.0 is the first major look into the challenges Trevor and Barbara Eyster are facing. Trevor and Barbara both give candid insight about the house situation, the arrest and its aftermath, and the things that need to be done moving forward. The supportive relationship dynamic between Trevor and Barbara is brought to the forefront, especially as Trevor has had to drop everything in his life to support his aunt.

2.title: Leak 1.5: Epic Laundry, Family Politics, Sponge's Agenda
2.plot: The viewer is given a glimpse of the challenges Trevor and Barb are facing. The house is shown, clearly having been not kept up by the caregiver in a very long time. Trevor explains his volunteer management and current projects.

3.title: Leak 1.75: Smokes & Bailbondsmen, Expensive Lies & Jailtime
3.plot: An uncensored look into Trevor's care of his aunt Barbara, as well as a glimpse into the paperwork nightmare he's faced.

4.title: Leak 2.1: in medias res: Fraudulent Eviction Notices & Bulletproof Vests: Barb's 2nd Abuser
4.plot: The legal state of the house is up in the air as an uncooperative trustee is becoming more aggressive. Further abuse on Aunt Barb is discovered, leading to more emotional strain on everybody involved.

5.title: Leak 1.8: After Sponge's Arrest: Barb's Medication Revelation
5.plot: After Trevor returns home after his brief and unjustified stint in jail, he is notified by his aunt that she had been deprived of her heart medicine during his absence. While the stress of the arrest night was getting to Barbara, she began having chest pains and needed her medicine. One of the bottles of her heart medicine had a different type of pill which would not have helped her condition. The only person with access to her pill bottles was her caregiver.

cast.name: Corps, Lance Corporal Jake 'The Piranha' U.S. Puppy

imdb.plot outline: Trevor's aunt, Barbara Eyster, has been living with Multiple Sclerosis. She had been provided a live-in caregiver who was paid to help care for her in her day-to-day life. On November 16, 2016, Trevor received an email from Barbara stating she was being evicted and had 3 days to remove her property from her house. When Trevor arrived to help, he was shocked by the condition of both Barbara and her house. He immediately moved in to help with her care. The day after Thanksgiving, Trevor returned to his aunt's home during an argument between the caregiver and his aunt. Multiple 911 calls were made when the caregiver refused to leave. During one of the 911 calls, the caregiver falsely claimed he was being threatened with a loaded gun. When the police arrived Trevor was arrested. Trevor posted bail, and the charges were later dropped. Trevor realized he needed to get the truth out to raise awareness for not only his aunt's situation but elder and dependent abuse as a whole. On December 19, 2016, the first #SpongeyLeaks video was released to show the public what had been going on behind closed doors in his aunt's house. The releases following look more into the details of the leading events, as well as what has happened in the days since the events of November 26.
